This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as named entity recognition and relation extraction, which are typically categorized under the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a neural, end-to-end model that integrates a pre-trained language model, which falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses information retrieval (cs.IR) as a related field, as well as named entity recognition (cs.NE) as a specific task.
